<font color="#FF0000">POEMS OF ROBERT H. DIRR JR.</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 21 14:50:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;Casualty #17&quot;<br><br>
A poem by Robert H. Dirr Jr.<br><br>
A soldier slumps, knocked down by an AK-47 slug.<br>
A corpsman works on the gaping chest wound.<br>
A friend whispers into his comrade's ear.<br>
A chaplain gives the last rites.<br>
A final word is uttered:<br>
&quot;Mom.&quot;<br>

<p><code>-- Bongo-Bob@msn.com  (Robert H. Dirr Jr.) </code><p>


